<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1322,284,390]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[264,387,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Comments</emphasis>
A mummy of the margarodid host (glued onto the same card with one of the 
<typeStatus box="[264,378,364,390]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">paratypes</typeStatus>
) has many exit holes, indicating that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="V. Trjapitzin &amp; S. Triapitsyn" authorityYear="2006" box="[816,933,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Brethesiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mojave">
<emphasis box="[816,933,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B. mojave</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a gregarious parasitoid.
</paragraph>
